marked: The ability to calculate is important for many aspects of social daily living
Impairment of calculation ability is also a common symptom in patients with Alzheimer’s disease, which can appear early in the course of the disease
91 Japanese patients with Alzheimer’s disease were selected
the NINCDS/ADRDA criteria for probable Alzheimer’s disease,
analyses showed that the test scores correlated significantly with nCMRglc in the left inferior parietal lobule
and in the left inferior temporal gyrus
